item.title: Portfolio
item.dc:creator: palejnatalia
item.content:encoded:
Food Recognition App (In Progress)

Description: AI based app which will recognize food from images and generate 3 recipes (where one is healthy)
Technologies: Python, TensorFlow, OpenCV, Flask, Groq AI
Skills: Image recognition, API integration

Read More

Current Development Stage
Currently, I have worked on two prototypes using different approaches. The below image was used for image recognition.

1. TensorFlow Prototype

In this version I wanted to test accuracy of pre-existing image recognition libraries. I have created methods to read, process and recognize items in the image. Then, I manually edit the request sent to Groq API for recipe generation.

The results showed that significant effort would be necessary to train the model for improved accuracy. This prototype led me to explore alternative options.

2. Groq Free AI API Prototype

In this prototype, I pass an image to the Groq API, which first identifies food items. In second query request, the recognized ingredients are then used to generate recipe suggestions. This method seems to be more effective, as Groq excels at accuracy in recognizing wide range of products.

Newsagent Management System

Description: Java based management system for handling orders, stock and customer information, using MySQL as the database backend
Technologies: Java, MySQL
Skills: Full-stack development, backend logic, database integration
Soft Skills: Team collaboration, problem-solving, communication, time management

Read More

In this project, we collaborated as a team of three to build a Newsagent Management System from scratch. The project required extensive planning and organization, where we collectively decided on the Agile, incremental approach. As a team, we mapped out system architecture and developed a detailed plan outlining the timeline, costs and increments for each phase. We also defined the classes and their interactions, creating an Activity Chart to guide the development process.

After planning, we divided the work, with each team member responsible for specific classes. Once individual components were completed, we merged the work and conducted thorough testing to ensure all classes integrated smoothly. The Java-based system included a user menu with role-based login options.

This project emphasized the importance of team collaboration, communication, and problem-solving, as we navigated the challenges of managing multiple contributors, resolving conflicts and merging branches. It enhanced our ability to work in a structured, methodical way while delivering a functional and user-friendly system. It also developed my leadership and decision-making skills in a collaborative setting, as I guided the project to completion while making sure every team member contributed equally to the final product.

Git Repository Link: [CLICK HERE]

Dog Application - Python

Description: The Dog Application is a cloud-based Python web application. It connects user-friendly front-end (reused from Dog Application - Server Side project) to a SQLAlchemy database, allowing users to manage dog profiles
Technologies: Python, Flask, SQLAlchemy, HTML/CSS
Skills: Python web development and database management, Docker deployment

Read More

The Dog Application was a personal project by my love for dogs, making the development process enjoyable. I learned to effectively manage my time and motivate myself to achieve my goals independently.

In this project, I utilized SQLAlchemy for database management, which enhanced my understanding of Python's database interactions. I also implemented version control (Git) to track changes, ensuring efficient development.

Deploying the application using Docker gave me valuable insights into containerization, allowing me to see how different components work seamlessly in a contained environment. Overall, this project reinforced my technical skills and highlighted the importance of self-discipline in achieving success.

Git Repository Link: [CLICK HERE]

Dog Application - Server Side

Description: Dog Application is a server-side project. It was built using Servlets for back-end functionality and JSP (JavaServer Pages) for front-end, it utilized MySQL to handle data storage and retrieval
Technologies: Java, Servlets, MySQL, JSP
Skills: Server-side programming with Java, building applications using Servlets, database management and SQL interactions

Read More

This project involved creating a robust backend system using Java Servlets to handle dog profiles. I have defined necessary classes and then implemented server-side logic to support functionality. I utilized MySQL for database management, which allowed me to efficiently store and retrieve data.

Working on this project improved my understanding of how Java Servlets operate and how different components of web application connect together. Although I faced challenges along the way, I was very happy with the final product.

item.title: Beyond The Code
item.dc:creator: palejnatalia
item.content:encoded:
Meet Lilly: My Little Partner-in-Crime

Lilly is my companion and the source of my endless joy. Whether she keeps bringing different toys to play or cuddling on the couch, she's always there to brighten my day.

"My little dog - a heartbeat at my feet" - Edith Wharton

Makeup

Fell in love with makeup during lockdown. It's my creative escape.

Makeup lets me express myself in ways I didn't expect, just like I didn't expect I will fall in love with it so much. It's not just about the final look, but the process of creating something that is uniquely "me".

Travelling

My love for travel is so strong that I plan everything in detail, from local food to adventures!

I'm not just passionate about travelling, I am a planner at heart. When I book a trip, it's not just about picking a destination - it's about the ultimate experience. I make countdown pages that are packed with plans and locations that I want to visit.

Baking

Baking is my stress relief. I find joy in creating something delicious.

Baking is my happy place - it's where I go to relax and feel accomplished. There's something about turning simple ingredients into cakes that makes the process so rewarding. I love baking for friends and family, as there's nothing better than seeing their smiles after biting into a homemade treat.

Sushi

What started as curiosity, had turned into a nearly weekly ritual

I'm officially sushi-obsessed! I love the creativity behind sushi-making. Finding the perfect balance of flavors and textures is a challenge I enjoy.

These interests make my life more enjoyable, helping me express myself and connect with the world around me.
